SIMPLE: ringtail
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ringtail
<hw>Ring"tail`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A bird having a distinct band of color across
the tail, as the hen harrier.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A light sail set abaft and beyong
the leech of a boom-and-gaff sail; -- called also
<altname>ringsail</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ringtail boom</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>a spar
which is rigged on a boom for setting a ringtail.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ring-tailed</ent>⟦br⟧
